# Transformative Use Cases

## For Developers 👨‍💻

### Before: Manual Documentation
```markdown
# API Endpoint Documentation (Outdated for 3 months)
## POST /users
- Parameters: name, email (password too?)
- Response: User object (which fields exactly?)
- Errors: 400, 500 (what do they mean?)
```

### After: {{product_name}} AI
```javascript
/**
 * Creates a new user in the system
 * Auto-documented by CloudDocs AI - Updated: 2 minutes ago
 *
 * @route POST /api/v3/users
 * @param {string} name - Full name (2-50 characters)
 * @param {string} email - Valid email (automatic verification)
 * @param {string} password - Minimum 8 characters, 1 uppercase, 1 number
 * @param {object} profile - Optional profile information
 * @returns {UserObject} Created user with ID and timestamps
 * @throws {ValidationError} 400 - Invalid data
 * @throws {ConflictError} 409 - Email already exists
 * @throws {ServerError} 500 - Internal server error
 *
 * @example
 * const newUser = await createUser({
 *   name: "Ana Garcia",
 *   email: "ana@company.com",
 *   password: "SecurePass123"
 * });
 */
```

